            <h3>Your Personal Information</h3>
            <p>This website may include web pages that give you the opportunity to provide us  with personal information about yourself. You do not have to provide us with  personal information if you do not want to; however, that may limit your  ability to use certain functions of this website or to request certain services  or information. ConcertoCare defines &ldquo;personal information&rdquo; as information  that we directly associate with or use to identify you. Personal information  may include your address, phone number, email address, fax number, or  information pertaining to a marketing program, online registration, or  financial account when associated with a person&rsquo;s name. Our definition does not  include &ldquo;aggregate personal information,&rdquo; which is information that we collect  about a group or category of persons or services, or &ldquo;de-identified  information,&rdquo; which is information from which we or our agents have removed any  information that can be used to specifically identify a person. This Privacy  Policy does not restrict or limit our collection or use of aggregate personal  information or de-identified information.</p>
            <p>We  may use personal information for several purposes such as:</p>
